description: Ryan Wesley Routh had previously been charged with possession of a firearm by a convicted felon and possession of a firearm with an obliterated serial number.
title: Ryan Routh, arrested near Trump's Florida golf course, is charged with attempted assassination

description: The Senate unanimously the legislation on Tuesday after it sailed through the House without any opposition. The measure now heads to President Joe Biden's desk for his signature.
title: Congress passes bill to boost presidential candidate security after apparent attempt on Trump's life

description: Nearly one year after the October 7 Hamas terror attack, Lester Holt speaks in an exclusive interview with a group whose loved ones remain in captivity in Gaza. Aviva Siegel was a hostage herself and says she fears for those still being held, including her husband Keith.
title: Former hostage: ‘I thought that I'm going to die all the time’

description: Tempe, Arizona, police are investigating what appears to be gunfire damage overnight at a Democratic Party-coordinated campaign office for Vice President Kamala Harris.
title: Harris campaign office damaged by gunfire in Arizona

description: Nebraska GOP Gov. Jim Pillen announced Tuesday he will not call a special legislative session to change how the state allocates its electoral votes.
title: In a blow to Trump, Nebraska governor will not call a special session to change state's electoral votes

description: With the death toll rising from Israel airstrikes targeting Hezbollah, thousands are now fleeing Southern Lebanon in search of safety. Israel insists it is not starting a new war in Lebanon but escalating one that has been going on for the past year. NBC’s Richard Engel reports for TODAY.
title: Thousands flee southern Lebanon as Israeli airstrikes kill hundreds

description: President Biden will take center-stage at the United Nations, addressing world leaders in one of the final and most consequential speeches of his presidency. The President is expected to address a series of global challenges from the climate crisis to conflicts in the Middle East and Ukraine. NBC’s Peter Alexander reports for TODAY.
title: Biden expected to address global conflicts in critical UN speech

description: President Joe Biden will address the United Nations General Assembly for the final time as commander in chief Tuesday morning amid the spiraling conflict in the Middle East, Russia’s ongoing war in Ukraine and growing global concerns about China’s influence.
title: Biden to deliver final U.N. General Assembly speech amid global turmoil as election nears

description: Lawyers for former President Donald Trump are pushing back against efforts by federal prosecutors to streamline arguments and potential appeals in his 2020 election interference case, arguing they could improperly influence the 2024 race for the White House.
title: Trump seeks to derail major court filing by federal prosecutors in election interference case
